      <body>
         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>
               <persName>
                  <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>oria Pr<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
               </persName>
               <supplied reason="lost">et</supplied>
               <lb n="2"/>
               <persName>
                  <name type="praenomen">
                     <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/>
                  </name>
                  <name type="gentilicium" key="Valerius">Valerius</name>
                  <name type="cognomen" key="Zosimus">Zo<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">simus</supplied>
                  </name>
               </persName>
               <lb n="3"/>sibi et suis lib<supplied reason="lost">ertis</supplied>
               <lb n="4"/>libertabusque o<supplied reason="lost">mnibus</supplied>.
            </ab>
            <!-- The marked up transcription goes here, surrounded by <ab> </ab> elements -->
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>[- - and -] Valerius Zo[simus?] (made this) for themselves and for a[ll] their
               free[dmen] and freedwomen.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 1: All but “oria Pr” of the first deceased’s gentilicium and cognomen is missing.</p>
            <p>Line 2: The abbreviation of Valerius’ praenomen is missing. Tuck supplements his
               cognomen as “Zosimus” based on frequency. </p>
         </div>
